page.title: 01Land North East of Guildford
page.content: This is an are of undulating countryside, mainly consising of farmlland,both arable and rough pasture, interspersed with woodland. There are seven villages around this district, namely Ripley and Ockham to the north, Send to the West, East and West Clandon to the south, west Horsley to the south and east Horsley to the east. he outuskirts of Ripley,Send,West Clandon and West Horsley infringe on the area where a few houses are shown in squares 1,9 nd12.There are several farms scattered about its district but some ae not private residences. The Send Detention Centre for juvenile offenders is situated in square 10. The A3 London to Portsmouth road crosses the north west corner and there are minor roads and lanes to the various villages.
